05869nam a22008655i 9783110891751DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20122006gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97831108917517 a10.1515/97831108917512doi  a(DE-B1597)46784  a(OCoLC)979849932  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 7aLIT0041702bisacsh0481pa830qDE-101  aGL 46182rvk0(DE-625)rvk/41501:1181000aJeremias Gotthelf - Wege zu einer neuen Ausgabe /chrsg. von Barbara Mahlmann-Bauer, Christian Zimmermann. 1aTübingen : bMax Niemeyer Verlag, c[2012] 4c©2006  a1 online resource (303 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aeditio / Beihefte ,x0939-5946 ;v240 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIm 150. Todesjahr von Jeremias Gotthelf begannen die Herausgeber mit der historisch-kritischen Edition seiner nicht-literarischen Schriften, die den ersten Baustein zu einer historisch-kritischen Gesamtausgabe von Gotthelfs Werken bilden. Über das Ziel und mögliche Wege, Gotthelfs Gesamtwerk in seinem historisch-politischen Kontext zu edieren und zu kommentieren, berieten sich die Herausgeber mit erfahrenen Editionsspezialisten und Gotthelf-Forschern. Die hier versammelten Beiträge öffnen Wege zu einem neuen Bild Gotthelfs, in dessen erzählerischem Werk seine Erfahrungen als streitbarer Pfarrer, Schulreformer, Journalist und Kalendermann eingegangen sind.  aOn the occasion of the 150th anniversary of Gotthelf's death, the editors began on an historical-critical edition of the author's non-literary works, representing the first stage in the eventual historical-critical edition of Gotthelf's entire oeuvre. The editors have engaged in extensive consultations with experienced editing experts and Gotthelf specialists on the objective of editing and commenting on Gotthelf's complete works in their historical and political context, and on potential avenues to be explored toward the realization of this endeavor. The articles assembled here indicate new approaches to Gotthelf, whose experiences as a committed clergyman, school reformer, journalist, and contributor to religious almanacs all found their way into his narratives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aDellsperger, Rudolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonien, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeilchenfeldt, Konrad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHahl, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHettche, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHildmann, Philipp W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohn, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandfester, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahlmann-Bauer, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahlmann-Bauer, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMorgenthaler, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReber, Alfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichter, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRusterholz, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteiger, Johann Anselm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomke, Hellmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTschopp, Silvia Serena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWiesmüller, Wo